USAGE
-----
To use Disaster Recovery Linux Server you always call the main script 
'/usr/sbin/drls':

----
# drls help
Usage: drls [-d] [-D] [-s] [-S] [-v] [-V] COMMAND [ARGS...]

Disaster Recovery Linux Server comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY; for details see
the GNU General Public License at: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html

Available options:
 -d           debug mode; log debug messages
 -D           debugscript mode; log every function call
 -s           simulation mode; show what scripts rear would include
 -S           step-by-step mode; acknowledge each script individually
 -v           verbose mode; show more output
 -V           version information

List of commands:

 addclient       blablablabla
 deleteclient    blablablabla
 modifyclient    blablablabla
 listclient      blablablabla
 addnetwork      blablablabla
 deletenetwork   blablablabla
 modifynetwork   blablablabla
 listnetwork     blablablabla
 addbackup       blablablabla
 deletebackup    blablablabla
 definebackup    blablablabla
 listbackup      blablablabla
 
 
 

Use 'drls -v help' for more advanced commands.
----

